<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FF5AFD5BFE87AE01" bold="true" box="[160,276,766,791]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" reason="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE4FFC8FF5AFC87FC2AA91C" blockId="7.[160,1156,766,1172]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FF5AFC87FF7CAE2C" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[160,239,802,826]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FF5AFC87FF7CAE2C" box="[160,239,802,826]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Hersilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FE8DFC87FDF9AE2C" authority="Simon, 1882" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1882" box="[375,618,802,826]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Murricia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FE8DFC87FE43AE2C" box="[375,464,802,826]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Murricia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE4FFC8FE26FC87FDF9AE2C" author="Simon E" box="[476,618,802,826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" pagination="207 - 260" refId="ref5045" refString="Simon E. 1882. II. Etude sur les arachnides de l ' Yemen meridional. In: Viaggio ad Assab nel Mar Rosso, dei signori G. Doria ed O. Beccari con il R. Aviso &quot; Esploratore &quot; dal 16 Novembre 1879 al 26 Febbraio 1880. Ann Mus Civ Stor Nat Genova. 18: 207 - 260." type="journal article" year="1882">
Simon, 
<quantity id="4C8F49AFFFE4FFC8FDC9FC87FDF9AE2C" box="[563,618,802,826]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.780279999999999" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" unit="in" value="1882.0">1882</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the number of cheliceral teeth (three promargianal, 6 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FED0FCE1FEA4AE4A" box="[298,311,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">–</emphasis>
10 retromarginal), two segmented metatarsi of legs I, II and IV, four pairs of dorsal abdominal muscular sigillae and the strong recurvation of anterior and posterior eye rows. Members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FE50FC2FFE6AAEB4" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[426,505,906,930]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FE50FC2FFE6AAEB4" box="[426,505,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Hersilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FCC6FC2FFC06AEB4" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1882" box="[828,917,906,930]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Murricia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FCC6FC2FFC06AEB4" box="[828,917,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Murricia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by their first pair of legs, which are usually longer than the second pair; their embolus, which does not complete a full revolution; and the presence of short and simple insemination ducts and accessory glands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE4FFC8FE97FC57FDF8A91C" author="Baehr B &amp; Baehr M" box="[365,619,1010,1034]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" pagination="347 - 391" refId="ref4400" refString="Baehr B, Baehr M. 1993. New species and new records of Hersiliidae from Australia, with an updated key to all Australian species (Arachnida: Araneae: Hersiliidae): fourth supplement to the revision of the Australian Hersiliidae. Rec West Aust Museum. 16: 347 - 391." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr and Baehr 1993</bibRefCitation>
; Rheims and Brescovit 2004).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE4FFC8FF3AFBB1FDD7A982" blockId="7.[160,1156,766,1172]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FF3AFBB1FE9CA93A" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[192,271,1044,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FF3AFBB1FE9CA93A" box="[192,271,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Hersilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
well differs from other hersiliids occurring in the Middle East by its large size, over 
<quantity id="4C8F49AFFFE4FFC8FF24FB92FEB7A959" box="[222,292,1079,1103]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
(other genera are smaller than 
<quantity id="4C8F49AFFFE4FFC8FD5CFB92FD7CA959" box="[678,751,1079,1103]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
), long spinnerets (posterior lateral spinnerets longer than carapace, whereas in other genera shorter than carapace) and two-segmented metatarsi I 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FE28FBD9FE4CA982" box="[466,479,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">–</emphasis>
II and IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36DB7C1FFE4FFC7FF5AFB64FDEFAC42" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="1454" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE4FFC8FF5AFB64FE8DA9CC" blockId="7.[160,1156,1217,1727]" box="[160,286,1217,1242]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">
