</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE4FFC8FF5AFB40FF66A8BC" blockId="7.[160,1156,1217,1727]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE4FFC8FF5AFB40FE3EA9EB" author="Baehr B &amp; Baehr M" box="[160,429,1253,1277]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" pagination="347 - 391" refId="ref4400" refString="Baehr B, Baehr M. 1993. New species and new records of Hersiliidae from Australia, with an updated key to all Australian species (Arachnida: Araneae: Hersiliidae): fourth supplement to the revision of the Australian Hersiliidae. Rec West Aust Museum. 16: 347 - 391." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr and Baehr (1993)</bibRefCitation>
revised the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FDC4FB40FD1EA9EB" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[574,653,1253,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FDC4FB40FD1EA9EB" box="[574,653,1253,1277]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Hersilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the 
<collectingRegion id="49B32AA8FFE4FFC8FD1FFB40FC00A9EB" box="[741,915,1253,1277]" country="Egypt" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
. The genus was split into 10 species groups: 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FE4AFAA2FDD6A854" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FE4AFAA2FDDBA809" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yin" authorityYear="1985" box="[432,584,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albomaculata">albomaculata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FDAFFAA2FD39A809" authorityName="Song &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="1982" box="[597,682,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">asiatica</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FD4DFAA2FCADA809" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1987" box="[695,830,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australiensis">australiensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FCB1FAA2FC35A809" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[843,934,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">caudata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FC49FAA2FC6CA809" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[947,1023,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facialis">facialis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FBF6FAA2FBECA809" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[1036,1151,1287,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flagellifera">flagellifera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FF5AFA8FFEA3A854" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[160,304,1322,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">impressifrons</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FEC7FA8FFE42A854" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[317,465,1322,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluensis">kinabaluensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FE25FA8FFDD6A854" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1895" box="[479,581,1322,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata">pectinata</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FD79FA8FFD48A854" authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1836" box="[643,731,1322,1346]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="savignyi">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FD79FA8FFD48A854" box="[643,731,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">savignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Revision of African 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FC3DFA8FFE48A873" authority="(Foord &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Foord &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FC3DFA8FFB85A854" box="[967,1046,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Hersilia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE4FFC8FBDCFA8FFE47A873" author="Foord SH &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman AS" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref4687" refString="Foord SH, Dippenaar-Schoeman AS. 2006. A revision of the Afrotropical species of Hersilia Audouin (Araneae: Hersiliidae). Zootaxa. 1347: 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="2006">Foord &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
revealed only five species groups, three of which occur in the 
<collectingRegion id="49B32AA8FFE4FFC8FF34FACAFEEAA891" box="[206,377,1391,1415]" country="Egypt" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
and two of which are endemic to Africa: the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FC7EFACAFC6CA891" authorityName="Foord &amp; Dippenaar-Schoeman" authorityYear="2006" box="[900,1023,1391,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aldabrensis">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FC7EFACAFC6CA891" box="[900,1023,1391,1415]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">aldabrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FBC1FACAFB10A891" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1967" box="[1083,1155,1391,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baforti">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FBC1FACAFB10A891" box="[1083,1155,1391,1415]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">baforti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC8E44AFFE4FFC7FF3AFA10FDEFAC42" blockId="7.[160,1156,1217,1727]" lastBlockId="8.[160,1155,142,340]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="1454" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">
Judging from the shape of the copulatory organs, the genus is not monophyletic. Species groups differ in the number of sclerites in the bulbus, from one (just corkscrew embolus) in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FEA3FA5FFE7FAB04" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[345,492,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluensis">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FEA3FA5FFE7FAB04" box="[345,492,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">kinabaluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group to several in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FD06FA5FFCC3AB04" authorityName="Song &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="1982" box="[764,848,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FD06FA5FFCC3AB04" box="[764,848,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">asiatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. In the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FC0AFA5FFB10AB04" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[1008,1155,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluensis">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FC0AFA5FFB10AB04" box="[1008,1155,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">kinabaluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group the embolus is directed anteriorly, while in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FCCAF9B8FC17AB23" authorityName="Song &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="1982" box="[816,900,1565,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asiatica">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FCCAF9B8FC17AB23" box="[816,900,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">asiatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group it is stretched subventrally, and in 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FE6EF99AFD96AB41" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[404,517,1599,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flagellifera">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FE6EF99AFD96AB41" box="[404,517,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">flagellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FDB3F99AFD31AB41" authorityName="Audouin" authorityYear="1826" box="[585,674,1599,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudata">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FDB3F99AFD31AB41" box="[585,674,1599,1623]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">caudata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups the embolus is coil shaped and 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FF5AF9C7FF35AB6C" box="[160,166,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">‘</emphasis>
wraps 
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FF13F9C7FF7CAB6C" box="[233,239,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">’</emphasis>
the tegulum. The embolus in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FD96F9C7FD62AB6C" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1987" box="[620,753,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australiensis">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FD96F9C7FD62AB6C" box="[620,753,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">australiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is S-shaped and very thick in comparison to that of other groups. 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FDB4F920FB93AB8B" authority="Baehr &amp; Baehr, 1993" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[590,1024,1669,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundaica">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FDB4F920FC9AAB8B" box="[590,777,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">Hersilia sundaica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE699BBFFE4FFC8FCE9F920FB93AB8B" author="Baehr B &amp; Baehr M" box="[787,1024,1669,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" pagination="347 - 391" refId="ref4400" refString="Baehr B, Baehr M. 1993. New species and new records of Hersiliidae from Australia, with an updated key to all Australian species (Arachnida: Araneae: Hersiliidae): fourth supplement to the revision of the Australian Hersiliidae. Rec West Aust Museum. 16: 347 - 391." type="journal article" year="1993">Baehr &amp; Baehr, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which has been assigned to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C779FC9FFE4FFC8FE4DF902FDD6ABA9" authorityName="Baehr &amp; Baehr" authorityYear="1993" box="[439,581,1703,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressifrons">
<emphasis id="B9033858FFE4FFC8FE4DF902FDD6ABA9" box="[439,581,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1453">impressifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, has a very complex embolus (embolic complex). The tegular (= median) apophysis also strongly differs in different groups. In some groups, the patella or tibia of male palp is modified, while in most of the groups the tibia and patella are not modified. Epigynes in different groups have considerable differences. Some groups have only one pair of round receptacles, while other species groups have three pairs. In many species, epigynal parts cannot be homologised. This genus was not reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F360A4DAFFEBFFC7FE03FE99FDB7AC42" box="[505,548,316,340]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="1454">Iran</collectingCountry>
before.
</paragraph>
